68
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:13,008
towards the sources of perception and also "evocations",

69
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:18,140
that is to say, the selection and direction of the consciousness

70
00:06:19,001 --> 00:06:22,004
towards the sources of retention.

71
00:06:23,005 --> 00:06:27,438
The voluntary and involuntary direction and selection of the consciousness

72
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:31,600
towards its different sources constitutes the function

73
00:06:31,006 --> 00:06:35,013
that has generically been referred to as "attention".

74
00:06:38,005 --> 00:06:43,006
2. Consciousness, attention and the ìIî

75
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,634
We term ìconsciousness,î

76
00:06:50,001 --> 00:06:54,134
the apparatus that coordinates and structures the sensations,

77
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:57,600
images and memories of the human psychism.

78
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:03,333
Furthermore, it is not possible to locate the consciousness in a precise place

79
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:10,339
in the central nervous system or at a certain cortical or subcortical point or depth.

80
00:07:11,002 --> 00:07:15,007
It is also not a matter of confusing specialized points of work,

81
00:07:15,007 --> 00:07:17,015
such as the ìcentersî,

82
00:07:18,005 --> 00:07:25,005
with the functional structures that can be verified throughout the totality of the nervous systemÖ

83
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,007
throughout the totality of the nervous system.

84
00:07:28,007 --> 00:07:30,440
For greater expository clarity,

85
00:07:31,133 --> 00:07:34,400
we designate as ìconscious phenomenaî

86
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:41,300
all that occurs in the different levels and states of vigil,

87
00:07:41,006 --> 00:07:46,539
semisleep and sleep, including those which are subliminal

88
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:52,300
i.e. those which occur at the limits of registers whether perceived,

89
00:07:52,003 --> 00:07:55,036
represented or remembered.

90
00:07:55,333 --> 00:08:00,337
Of course, when speaking of the ìsubliminalî

91
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:08,400
we are not referring to those supposed ìsubconsciousî or ìunconsciousî.

92
00:08:08,008 --> 00:08:13,009
Often the consciousness is confused with the ìI,î

93
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:20,000
when in reality the latter doesnít have a corporeal base,

94
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:25,700
as does the consciousness, which though may be diffuse, does have a corporeal base,

95
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,333
does have a physical base,

96
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:32,010
Ö but it seems the I is another storyÖ

97
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:43,002
as occurs with that which can be identified as the registering

98
00:08:43,002 --> 00:08:46,003
and coordinating "apparatus" of the human psychism.

99
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:48,700
We previously stated that:

100
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:53,500
ìÖThis register of the own identity of the consciousness

101
00:08:53,005 --> 00:08:56,008
is given by the data of the senses, the data of memory,

102
00:08:56,008 --> 00:09:04,941
and a peculiar configuration that gives to the consciousness the illusion of permanence,

103
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:11,200
in spite of the continual changes that it can verify within itself.

104
00:09:12,004 --> 00:09:19,007
This illusory configuration of identity and permanence is the "Iî.

105
00:09:22,001 --> 00:09:25,001
It is frequently seen in altered states of consciousness,

106
00:09:25,001 --> 00:09:28,005
that while the consciousness maintains itself in vigil, specific impulses

107
00:09:28,005 --> 00:09:32,013
that should arrive as registers are blocked,

108
00:09:33,003 --> 00:09:38,011
and the notion of the ìIî undergoes an alteration or an estrangement.

109
00:09:40,004 --> 00:09:41,004
In this situation,

110
00:09:41,004 --> 00:09:46,004
the ìIî is registered as located in the external limit-zones

111
00:09:46,004 --> 00:09:52,009
of the space of representation and at a certain ìdistanceî from the habitual ìIî

112
00:09:52,009 --> 00:09:54,010
Ö distance in quotations marks.

113
00:09:56,433 --> 00:10:01,436
The subject can experience themselves

114
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:06,600
registering and feeling phenomena that come from the external world

115
00:10:06,006 --> 00:10:10,011
although, rigorously speaking, these are not phenomena of perception

116
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:13,342
but rather representation.

117
00:10:14,005 --> 00:10:18,738
These phenomena, where representation is substituted for perception

118
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:24,100
and as such located within an ìexternal spaceî

119
00:10:24,001 --> 00:10:30,434
towards whose limit the ìIî moves, we refer to as ìprojectionsî.

120
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:40,600
3. Spatiality and temporality of the phenomena of consciousness

121
00:10:42,008 --> 00:10:48,341
In active vigil, the ìIî locates itself in the more external zones of the space of representation,Ö

122
00:10:50,008 --> 00:10:52,010
I see you! Do you exist?

123
00:10:56,233 --> 00:10:57,500
Hallucination!

124
00:10:59,008 --> 00:11:05,009
In active vigil, the ìIî locates itself in the more external zones of the space of representation,

125
00:11:06,002 --> 00:11:11,008
ìlostî in the limits of external sense of touch,

126
00:11:12,001 --> 00:11:14,007
but if I have an apperception of something that I see,

127
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:19,440
the register of the ìIî shifts.

128
00:11:23,006 --> 00:11:26,008
In this moment I could say to myself:

129
00:11:27,001 --> 00:11:36,001
ìFrom where I am I see an external object that I register within my bodyî.

130
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:44,842
Even though I am connected with the external world through the senses

131
00:11:46,001 --> 00:11:56,034
there exists a division between spaces, and it is in the internal space that I locate the ìIî.

132
00:11:59,007 --> 00:12:02,011
If I subsequently have an apperception of my breathing

133
00:12:04,004 --> 00:12:05,011
I might say to myselfÖ

134
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:10,335
parenthesis (this is what I say to myself):

135
00:12:11,008 --> 00:12:16,011
ìI experience within me the movement of my lungs.

136
00:12:20,002 --> 00:12:26,008
I am inside my body but I am not inside my lungsî.

137
00:12:28,004 --> 00:12:34,337
It is clear that I register a distance between the ìIî and the lungs,

138
00:12:35,008 --> 00:12:41,008
not only because I register the ìIî in the head which is far from the thoracic cage

139
00:12:42,002 --> 00:12:44,735
but because in all cases of internal perception,

140
00:12:45,004 --> 00:12:49,437
as may occur with a toothache or headache,

141
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,009
these registers will always be at a ìdistanceî,

142
00:12:54,002 --> 00:12:58,002
at a ìdistanceî from me as observer.

143
00:13:02,007 --> 00:13:11,240
But here we are not interested in this ìdistanceî between me and the object,

144
00:13:12,002 --> 00:13:13,002
rather what we are interested in

145
00:13:13,002 --> 00:13:16,005
is the ìdistanceî from the ìIî towards the external world

146
00:13:16,005 --> 00:13:20,008
and from the ìIî towards the internal world.

147
00:13:21,006 --> 00:13:23,007
In both directions there is a distance,

148
00:13:23,007 --> 00:13:27,940
and weíre interested in this distance, in that it presents itself and speaksÖ

149
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:33,200
Certainly we could point out very subtle

150
00:13:33,002 --> 00:13:36,009
nuances in the variability of the ìspatialî positions of the ìIî,

151
00:13:36,009 --> 00:13:37,014
but here we are highlighting

152
00:13:38,004 --> 00:13:42,137
the diametrical locations of the ìIî in each of the mentioned cases.

153
00:13:42,008 --> 00:13:45,011
In this description, we can also say that the ìIî

154
00:13:46,001 --> 00:13:50,234
can be located in the interior of the space of representation

155
00:13:50,009 --> 00:13:52,442
but in the kinesthetic tactile limits

156
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:56,600
that give the notion of the external world and inversely,

157
00:13:56,833 --> 00:14:03,400
in the coenesthetic tactile limits that give the notion of the internal world.

158
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:11,041
In any case, we can use the image of a biconcave film

159
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:16,008
as the limit between worlds,

160
00:14:17,001 --> 00:14:21,006
a biconcave film as the limit between worlds

161
00:14:21,009 --> 00:14:24,010
that dilates or contracts,

162
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:34,500
and in this way focuses or blurs the register of external and internal objects.

163
00:14:35,007 --> 00:14:39,007
The attention is directed more or less intentionally

164
00:14:39,007 --> 00:14:43,014
towards the registers of the external or internal senses in vigil.

165
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:48,400
This management of its direction is lost in semisleep,

166
00:14:48,008 --> 00:14:52,008
sleep or even in altered states of vigil

167
00:14:53,033 --> 00:14:55,000
since in all these levels and states

168
00:14:55,000 --> 00:15:01,009
reversibility is affected by phenomena and registers that are imposed on the consciousness.

169
00:15:02,006 --> 00:15:08,011
It is very evident that in the constitution of the ìIî are taking part not only memory,

170
00:15:09,001 --> 00:15:11,008
perception and representation

171
00:15:12,033 --> 00:15:17,500
but also the position of the attention in the space of representation.

172
00:15:18,004 --> 00:15:22,237
Consequently, we are not speaking about a substantial ìIî

173
00:15:22,009 --> 00:15:28,015
but rather an epiphenomena of the activity of the consciousness.

174
00:15:30,005 --> 00:15:32,938
This ìI - attentionî

175
00:15:33,007 --> 00:15:36,010
seems to carry out the function of coordinating the activities of the consciousness

176
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:41,733
with oneís own body and with the world in general.

177
00:15:43,002 --> 00:15:47,005
The registers of the position and elapsing of mental phenomena

178
00:15:47,005 --> 00:15:54,009
overlap in, and also become independent of, this mental coordination.

179
00:15:55,001 --> 00:16:00,006
In this way, the metaphor of the ìIî ends up taking on identity

180
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:03,933
as if it existed

181
00:16:06,004 --> 00:16:12,237
and ìsubstantiality,î becoming independent of the structure of the functions of the consciousness.

182
00:16:13,002 --> 00:16:19,002
On the other hand, the repeated registers and recognition of the action of attention

183
00:16:19,005 --> 00:16:21,938
goes being configured in the human being from very early

184
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:27,200
on in the measure that the child arranges more or less voluntary

185
00:16:27,002 --> 00:16:31,002
directions towards the external world and towards the intrabody.

186
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:37,500
Gradually, along with the management of the body and certain internal functions,

187
00:16:38,003 --> 00:16:41,336
the punctual presence is strengthened

188
00:16:41,009 --> 00:16:47,012
as is a copresence in which the register of oneís own ìIî is constituted

189
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:55,500
as concentrator and background of all mental activity.

190
00:16:56,001 --> 00:17:02,234
We are in the presence of the great illusion of the consciousness which we call ìIî.

191
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:08,440
We should now consider the location of the ìIî in the different levels of consciousness.

192
00:17:09,004 --> 00:17:15,011
In vigil the ìIî occupies a central position

193
00:17:16,008 --> 00:17:21,541
given by the availability of the attention and reversibility.

194
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:26,700
This varies considerably in semisleep,

195
00:17:26,009 --> 00:17:28,942
when the impulses that come from the external senses

196
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:35,837
tend to become weakened or fluctuate between the external world and a generalized coenesthesia.

197
00:17:37,001 --> 00:17:41,634
It is during sleep with images that the ìIî internalizes itself.

198
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:49,141
Lastly, it is in vegetative sleep that the register of the ìIî disappears.

199
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:55,007
A footnote: In the ìparadoxal dreamî or dream with images,

200
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,008
the register of the ìIî becomes ìdistantî from the external world

201
00:17:59,008 --> 00:18:03,008
and dilutes itself in unconnected images to the point of disappearing

202
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:09,004
in a situation which is difficult to control for the dreamer.

203
00:18:09,008 --> 00:18:11,016
In terms of deep vegetative sleep,

204
00:18:12,009 --> 00:18:18,642
electroencelographics show a complete lack of images.

205
00:18:20,001 --> 00:18:24,008
Neither can REM (Rapid Eye Movement) be verified,

206
00:18:24,008 --> 00:18:27,009
which coincides with a later forgetting of the psychic events

207
00:18:27,009 --> 00:18:34,014
that occurred in a total forgetting of the ìIî.

208
00:18:39,009 --> 00:18:42,442
The transformations of the impulses in vigilic reveries

209
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:46,334
appear in the sequences of free association

210
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:50,700
with numerous allegorical, symbolic and signic translations

211
00:18:50,007 --> 00:18:55,012
that make up the special language of the images of the coenesthesia.

212
00:18:56,933 --> 00:19:01,937
Of course we are referring to the uncontrolled sequences of images

213
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,933
typical of the associative pathways and not to the imaginary constructions,

214
00:19:07,933 --> 00:19:10,600
not to the imaginary constructions

215
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:15,700
that follow a, more or less, premeditated development,

216
00:19:15,009 --> 00:19:18,016
nor are we referring to the translation of impulses channeled through the abstractive paths

217
00:19:19,006 --> 00:19:23,139
which also are manifested as symbolical and signic images.

218
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:27,400
Impulses, transforming themselves in different levels

219
00:19:27,004 --> 00:19:30,005
also cause the register of the ìIî

220
00:19:30,008 --> 00:19:35,008
to vary in depth and superficiality in the space of representation.

221
00:19:36,001 --> 00:19:37,003
To sketch this out

222
00:19:37,003 --> 00:19:41,009
we could point out that psychic phenomena are always registered

223
00:19:42,003 --> 00:19:48,011
not only between the ìspatialî coordinates x and y

224
00:19:49,001 --> 00:19:52,234
but also in respect to z;

225
00:19:52,006 --> 00:19:58,011
ìzî being the depth of the register in the space of representation.

226
00:19:59,007 --> 00:20:02,011
Of course the register of any phenomenon

227
00:20:03,001 --> 00:20:08,007
is experienced in the tridimensionality of the space of representation

228
00:20:09,001 --> 00:20:20,001
according its greater externality or interiority with respect to the impulsesí depth,

229
00:20:20,001 --> 00:20:25,002
vertical height, and horizontal lateral position

230
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:29,433
ósomething that can be verified through apperception or representing impulses

231
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:38,300
originating from the external world, the intrabody or the memory.

232
00:20:38,009 --> 00:20:40,018
Avoiding the complications of the descriptions proper to Phenomenology

233
00:20:41,008 --> 00:20:47,009
we should now consider some topics which it has exhaustively studied.

234
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:51,839
We say that in vigil the fields of presence and copresence

235
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:58,434
allow us to locate phenomena within a temporal succession,

236
00:20:59,004 --> 00:21:01,004
establishing the relation of events

237
00:21:01,004 --> 00:21:04,837
from the present moment where I am located

238
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:09,010
along with previous moments from which the flow of my consciousness comes

239
00:21:10,003 --> 00:21:16,336
as well as subsequent moments, to which this flow is directed.

240
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:27,500
In any case, the present instant is the barrier of temporality

241
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,007
and even though I cannot give an account of it

242
00:21:29,007 --> 00:21:34,013
because when I think about it I count only on the retention of what has happened

243
00:21:35,006 --> 00:21:36,439
in the dynamic of my consciousness,

244
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:45,000
its apparent "fixity" permits me to go ìbackì toward the phenomena that are no longer

245
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:50,000
